Job Responsibility
Kubernetes infrastructure engineer

I operate with high degree of technical independence, designing, implementing,automating and stabilizing the cloud native architecture designed by me,i define technical roadmap, making architectural decisions,and ensuring platform design aligns with well architect framework, CNCF and business requirements.
I identify platform gaps, design solutions, and help assign implementation activities to other team members as part of overall architecture(example, our own IPAM/proxsync/netbox or envoy/consul-kuma client connection). Currently also knowledge transfer on the architecture design with workshops, meanwhile i remain accountable for the final outcome, system stability and long-term maintainability.


Motivation
I am highly motivated by designing and implementing complex, secure, and scalable infrastructure end-to-end, my main strength lies in translating business and platform requirements into resilient technical solutions, particularly in constrained and security-first environments such as talos os clusters.

Cloud architecture, software-defined networking, service mesh, devOps and desecOps motivate me a lot. i would like to spend more time on system design, architecture evolution , and long term platform strategy, and less time on manual or operations tasks.

Also is important to me that my role, responsibilities, technical delivery and compensation accurately reflect the level of technical ownership and accountability i carry, especially when delivering critical infrastructure that enables other team to work effectively.


Learning & Development

I would like to develop further my expertise in platform-level security and governance for systems especially immutable, in areas as policy-as-code, security benchmarks, automated compliance enforcement

key focus areas include Kubernetes policy engines(like admission control concepts), security auditing aligned with CIS benchmarks, and deeper integration of secrets management and identity based access control.

i would also like to continue developing architectural leadership skills, including system design communication, devOps and desecOps toolset and end to end integration, as well as risk assessment, and cross-team technical alignment.
Also take certifications that align with current role, and technical tools i forsee(ex: cka, ckd,cks, terraform pro etc).



